Companion (bottom-screen travel) — export + control bridge for the native TravelWindow
(GM_Travel). Mirrors companion-repair-export.patch (a mGuiModeStates single-mode window, not a
WindowManager member).

Outbound (COMPANION_TRAVEL_*, streamed one small line each for 4096-byte flush safety), emitted
from TravelWindow::setPtr -> companionExportOpen(): OPEN:<npcName> -> COMPANION_PLAYER_GOLD:<amount>
-> DEST:<index>|<destinationName>|<cost>|<interior 1/0>* -> END. index is the destination's ordinal
position among mDestinationsView's children (== transport order). No separate cache: addDestination
already stores each destination's name/price/interior as widget UserStrings (price is the
merchant-adjusted cost it computed), which companionExportOpen reads back and companionTravelByIndex
reuses. Stable handle because GM_Travel pauses the sim (only a travel mutates the set, which ends it).

Inbound: a file-static gCompanionTravelWindow (set in the ctor) plus two extern "C" bridges —
companionTravelGo / companionTravelCancel — let drainCompanionCommands drive travel from CMP:travel_*
commands. companionTravelByIndex calls the native onTravelButtonClick(child) UNCHANGED (full
affordability/gold/time/follower-teleport path — not reimplemented). Each bridge no-ops unless
containsMode(GM_Travel) (stale-window guard). Prices come from MechanicsManager::getBarterOffer and
the teleport moves followers (ActionTeleport) — native-only, the reason this must be a native bridge.

Close signal: the native window is HIDDEN the moment the mode opens in DS mode
(companion-hide-travel-on-dsmode.patch), so the usual visible->hidden onClose() transition never
fires. COMPANION_TRAVEL_CLOSED is emitted explicitly, once-guarded (gCompanionTravelSessionOpen),
from every close path: travel success (onTravelButtonClick), the companionTravelCancel bridge
(bottom-screen Cancel), exit() (B/Escape), onCancelButtonClicked (native Cancel, Vanilla), and
onReferenceUnavailable (NPC despawn/death).
